Mexican Stocks: Alfa SAB, Grupo Mexico SAB Shares Advance

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-05-25T16:28:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/mexican-stocks-alfa-sab-grupo-mexico-sab-shares-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:33 a.m.  New York  time.  The IPC index rose 0.1 percent to 35,411.20.  Alfa SAB (ALFAA MM), the world’s largest producer of
aluminum engine heads, jumped 1.7 percent to 164.49 pesos.
General Motors Co. said it will invest $69 million and add 2,500
jobs to start making two new models at the Detroit plant that
builds the Chevrolet Volt plug-in hybrid.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, advanced 0.8 percent to 40.31 pesos. Copper
futures for July delivery rose as much as 2.8 percent on the
Comex in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  